        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 4:12PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 411 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southeast of McCall, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust reducing
visibility. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Lake Fork Guard Station around 430 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

If on or near Payette Lake or Cascade Reservoir, get out of the
water and move indoors or inside a vehicle. Remember, lightning can
strike out to 10 miles from the parent thunderstorm. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Move to
safe shelter now! Do not be caught on the water in a thunderstorm.</instruction>
